<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-08-1279 </DOCNO><TEXT>The U.S. Geological Survey (USGS) coal program consists of three majorparts: 1. Studies of the sedimentary rocks containing the Nation's coalresource and their environments of deposition. 2. Characterization ofpeat, lignite, and coal according to the type and composition of theirorganic and inorganic materials. 3. The National Coal Resources DataSystem (NCRDS), a computerized bank of information on more than 100,000drill holes and measured sections and 10,000 coal and rock samples.</TEXT></DOC>